<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The class tries to load incompatible magic.mime (since PHP 5.3.11 there is a new libmagic version), causing errors thrown by magic, for example:
finfo_open() [<a href="function.finfo-open">function.finfo-open</a>]: Warning: string extension `B' invalid
and about thousand more similar to this one.</p>

<p>A simialr issue was mentioned in this ticket: <a href="http://framework.zend.com/issues/browse/ZF-10461">http://framework.zend.com/issues/browse/ZF-10461</a>, but it never got fixed.
I suggest that solution from Jarek Nowisz should be included in ZF 1.11. I tested it and it works.</p>

<p>"Beginning with version 5.3.0, finfo is part of PHP and uses internal magic file, ZF should not try to load it."</p>

